CERTIFIED SAFE: Drive safe knowing your Frozen high back booster car seat exceeds the Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS 213) and boasts a BEST BET BOOSTER rating from the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety (IIHS) CUP HOLDER: Equipped with a cup holder so your child can enjoy their beverage or snack at any time during the ride
body.description: Your child will love hopping into the car knowing they are safe and as cool as they can be, in their very own Frozen car seat! Now they can ride along with the iconic characters from Disney's Frozen, like Anna, Elsa, and everyone's favorite snowman, Olaf! The Kids Embrace Disney Frozen high-back booster Car Seat has been rigorously tested and exceeds federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS 213), Plus it was given a “Best Bet” Rating by the Insurance Institute for Highway Safety. The high-back booster is approved for use by children over 4 years old weighing 40 to 100 pounds and 38 to 57 inches in height. It easily converts from a high-back booster to a backless booster for children over 4 years old weighing 40 to 100 pounds and 40 to 57 inches in height. The headrest adjusts to two different positions to accommodate your growing child. The booster back features an integrated shoulder-belt positioning guide, and when your child is ready for the backless configuration, there is a belt-positioning clip that keeps your vehicle shoulder belt at the correct height for maximum safety. The contoured seat is comfortable for long rides, and the cushioned seat cover is machine-washable for easy cleaning. The Frozen high-back booster comes with one cup holder that is easy to attach on either side of the base, for easy access for a drink, snack, or your child’s favorite soft toy. It measures 17.25 by 14.5 by 25-1/2 inches (L x W x H) (headrest down) to 17-1/4 by 14-1/2 by 28 inches (L x W x H) (headrest up), and it weighs 12 pounds.

Buen producto, el tamaño muy bien, la instalación muy fácil, solo me hubiera gustado un poco más acojinado.

reviews.reviewTitle: Cómodo y seguro para niños mayores de 3 años
reviews.reviewText: Este es un gran asiento para niños mayores. Yo diría que es para niños de 3 a 4 años en adelante. Lo que me gusta de este asiento es que mantiene presionado el cinturón de seguridad para que no quede en la cara o el cuello de los niños. El asiento coloca el cinturón de seguridad en una posición cómoda para los niños.Una vez que su hijo es más alto y puede colocar su cinturón de seguridad por sí solo, puede quitar la parte posterior del asiento y usar la parte inferior del asiento solo para elevarlo. Esto es probablemente para cuando su hijo tiene alrededor de 6-7.Este asiento es ideal para niños mayores que han crecido fuera de su asiento original. No es bueno para bebés o niños pequeños, ya que no ofrece la protección adecuada para ellos.
